title: For Sale:  Zenith Z-5RS
postcontent: The purchaser must be a Virginia resident and be able to prove that with a driver's license. Otherwise, you will have to come with me to my local shop to transfer it, and they charge $50.This is a Zenith Z-5RS, purchased from Atlantic Firearms, Sold by Zenith Arms, and Produced by MKE out of Turkey. It is the closest clone of the HK MP5 I know of. It is an HK quality clone as well. It is made using original HK tooling and the factory was originally supervised by HK Engineers. It is compatible with almost of HK made parts, including stocks and foreends. I wanted to file the paperwork and get a few American-made parts to make it legal, and SBR it. It is also Auto-sear compatible. It does have a paddle mag release as well.The firearm itself isn't very old. It was purchased in March, constructed in February. It comes with everything it came with upon purhcase: hard case, three 30-round magazines, picatinny rail and mounting screws, arm-loop sling, cleaning kit, 'birthdate' paperwork and manual. I am also including a magazine pouch that holds all three mags. I've put 250 rounds through it with not a single failure, a testament to the fluted chamber design. I only recovered about 25% of the brass since the roller-delayed blowback action flings most of them into orbit. I cleaned it after 200 rounds, and fired another 50, so the firearm hasn't been cleaned after that. The bore and crown are completely intact, and the firearm is entirely mechanically sound. It just needs a good cleaning. There is no damage to the gun either, aside from a few minor scratches from putting the firearm down and picking it up from a plastic table.I'm pretty firm on the $1500 price tag, as you won't find a cheaper one anywhere, accept through private sale like this one. I'd be willing to reduce the price in exchange for a stock used pistol, such as a glock 17, 19, or 21. I'm willing to consider any used handguns, but I'd prefer it to keep to a common caliber, with the exception of a PMR-30. I'm specifically looking for a Kel-Tec PMR-30 if you have one to exchange. Not accepting trades other than a minor one to relieve some of the pricetag, as I'm aware it's a premium firearm.

title: For Sale:  EAA Witness Pavona 9mm
postcontent: Eaa Witness "Pavona" Lavender 9mm Semiautomatic. Comes with one mag, case and accessories shown in pics. Very nice condition. Used, like new. Licensed FFL. Shipping to US FFL $25 flat rate. Or local pick up at our store in Hudson Fl.  For the discerning shooter who appreciates Italian design and craftsmanship. The new WITNESS PAVONA POLYMER PISTOL is compact, easy to load, easy to control and enjoyable to use. From its inception in the world famous Italian Valley of the Guns, the Witness Pavona offers a lightweight, ergonomic grip in a distinct, compact, smooth, sparkling polymer frame; with integral checkering and sculptured, contoured lines. Tanfoglio kept the traditional external hammer so when the hammer is cocked with the safety engaged, before slide movement, the hammer spring is depressed thus allowing the slide to move easier during loading. Tanfoglio engineers also fine-tuned the hammer and recoil springs to allow for smoother function in addition to adding unique slide-gripping areas to enhance the overall pistol function, feel and ease of use. The WITNESS PAVONA is beautifully designed, elegantly packaged and sparkles when you hold it; a sophisticated pistol for any shooter.  Features: Compact Polymer Semi-Automatic; Low Profile, White Dot, Windage Adjustable Sight; Double Action/Single Action Trigger; Enhanced Slide Serrations; Reversable Mag Release; Polymer Frame; Lightened Recoil and Hammer Springs for reduced felt recoil and loading
